&gt;&gt; Neal Barnard: OK.

00:51:09.130 --> 00:51:13.670
Um, oil is, um -- is high in
calories as any other fat.

00:51:13.670 --> 00:51:15.720
So if a person is trying to
lose weight, we not only want

00:51:15.720 --> 00:51:18.710
to avoid the animal fat, it's good
to keep the vegetable oils low too.

00:51:18.710 --> 00:51:23.280
So even extra virgin -- even extra
extra virgin olive oil still has

00:51:23.280 --> 00:51:25.200
nine calories per gram.

00:51:25.200 --> 00:51:26.630
You remember that number?

00:51:26.630 --> 00:51:29.320
Um, so for weight loss it's
good to keep fatty foods low

00:51:29.320 --> 00:51:31.970
and that includes things like
peanut butter and even guacamole,

00:51:31.970 --> 00:51:34.280
which has a lot of fat in it.

00:51:34.280 --> 00:51:36.870
Um, vegetable oils are
different from animal fat

00:51:36.870 --> 00:51:39.110
in that they don't have
a lot of saturated fat

00:51:39.110 --> 00:51:41.550
that raises your blood cholesterol.

00:51:41.550 --> 00:51:44.230
And our friends in
Spain and in Italy argue

00:51:44.230 --> 00:51:46.900
for what they will call
the Mediterranean diet,

00:51:46.900 --> 00:51:49.140
which is not a butter type diet.

00:51:49.140 --> 00:51:51.280
It's more an olive oil type diet.

00:51:51.280 --> 00:51:53.660
And they will point
to heart benefits

00:51:53.660 --> 00:51:54.960
from the Mediterranean diet.

00:51:54.960 --> 00:51:56.710
Now Mediterranean diet
isn't just oil.

00:51:56.710 --> 00:51:59.010
It's also less meat,
more vegetables.

00:51:59.010 --> 00:52:02.380
Uh, some people will argue that
red wine is a key ingredient.

00:52:02.380 --> 00:52:05.300
Um, all these things may work
together to create health effects.

00:52:05.300 --> 00:52:08.010
So oil is better than animal
fat, but for weight loss,

00:52:08.010 --> 00:52:10.970
that's one reason to
keep it kind of low.

