00:52:18.040 --> 00:52:19.950
&gt;&gt; Just sometimes you'll
see articles that say

00:52:19.950 --> 00:52:24.970
that there are [inaudible]
medical, um, problems with soy.

00:52:24.970 --> 00:52:26.270
&gt;&gt; Neal Barnard: OK.

00:52:26.270 --> 00:52:29.520
I'm really glad that you
asked that because, um,

00:52:29.520 --> 00:52:31.120
the argument goes like this.

00:52:31.120 --> 00:52:35.820
Soy has estrogens in it that will
cause boys to become effeminate

00:52:35.820 --> 00:52:37.480
and cause girls to
have a higher risk

00:52:37.480 --> 00:52:39.210
of breast cancer is
what they'll say.

00:52:39.210 --> 00:52:41.370 position:56%
Um, the -- here's the truth of this.

00:52:41.370 --> 00:52:46.870 position:56%
Back in 1921 some compounds were
identified in soy called isoflavones

00:52:46.870 --> 00:52:48.830
and they look vaguely
like sex hormones.

00:52:48.830 --> 00:52:50.530
They are not sex hormones.

00:52:50.530 --> 00:52:52.370
But they look vaguely like it.

00:52:52.370 --> 00:52:57.070
And if you, however, look at
men who consume a lot of soy, A,

00:52:57.070 --> 00:53:01.530
they are not effeminate, B, there
is no reduction in fertility

00:53:01.530 --> 00:53:06.010
as you can quickly see when you go
to any country like China or Japan

00:53:06.010 --> 00:53:08.940 position:56%
where soy is a big part of the diet.

00:53:08.940 --> 00:53:11.760
Fertility has not been impaired.

00:53:11.760 --> 00:53:15.250
Um, but most importantly when
it comes to breast cancer,

00:53:15.250 --> 00:53:21.460
there have now been I believe at
least 35 or 40 studies on women

00:53:21.460 --> 00:53:22.840
who consume a lot of soy.

00:53:22.840 --> 00:53:26.800
Their breast cancer risk
is cut by about 30% to 40%.

00:53:26.800 --> 00:53:29.870
In other words, soy somehow
has the opposite effect.

00:53:29.870 --> 00:53:32.790
And I don't know why and I'm not
even necessarily pushing soy.

00:53:32.790 --> 00:53:34.090
Um, it's very convenient.

00:53:34.090 --> 00:53:37.050
You know, you're better off with
soy sausage than pork sausage.

00:53:37.050 --> 00:53:39.950
Uh, you don't need it, but
women who consume a fair amount

00:53:39.950 --> 00:53:43.410
of soy have much less risk
of developing breast cancer.

00:53:43.410 --> 00:53:47.740
And women who have had
breast cancer in the past,

00:53:47.740 --> 00:53:52.210 position:56%
if they consume more soy, their risk
of reoccurrence is about 30% less.

00:53:52.210 --> 00:53:54.000
And that's important because
a lot of them are told

00:53:54.000 --> 00:53:56.750
by their well-meaning,
but ill-informed doctor --

00:53:56.750 --> 00:54:00.250
I read somewhere you shouldn't have
soy if you've had breast cancer

00:54:00.250 --> 00:54:03.870
and the women who avoid soy have
the highest reoccurrence rate.

00:54:03.870 --> 00:54:06.320
So, I'm not pushing soy,
but it -- it does --

00:54:06.320 --> 00:54:08.100
it seems to have these
health benefits.

